verbs.description: untreasure (third-person singular simple present untreasures, present participle untreasuring, simple past and past participle untreasured)

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete, poetic) To despoil of treasure.
(transitive, obsolete, poetic) To display or set forth.
examples: the quaintness with which he untreasured, as by rote, the stores of his memory
